'''Bit nibbler''', or '''nibbler''', is a [[computer program]] that defeats some early ([[1980s]]) [[copy protection#Copy_protection_for_computer_software|software copy protection]] schemes by reading the [[floppy disk|disk]] one [[bit]] at a time, and directly interacting with the [[disk drive]] [[computer hardware|hardware]].

